<h2>Oyster cards</h2>

<p>An Oyster card is a smart card that you add money to, so you can <a href="/fares-and-payments/fares2018/how-to-pay-and-where-to-buy-tickets-and-oyster/pay-as-you-go">pay as you go</a>.</p>

<p>You can pay as you go to travel on bus, Tube, tram, DLR, London Overground, TfL Rail, Emirates Air Line and River Bus.</p>

<p>You can also travel on most National Rail services in London and some <a href="/fares-and-payments/fares2018/find-fares/national-rail-fares-beyond-zone-9">outside London</a>.</p>

<p>You can also add:</p>

<ul>
	<li><a href="/fares-and-payments/fares2018/how-to-pay-and-where-to-buy-tickets-and-oyster/travelcards-and-group-tickets">Travelcard</a></li>
	<li><a href="/fares-and-payments/fares2018/how-to-pay-and-where-to-buy-tickets-and-oyster/bus-and-tram-pass">Bus &amp; Tram Pass</a></li>
	<li><a href="/fares-and-payments/fares2018/free-and-discounted-travel">Discounts</a></li>
</ul>

<h2>How to use</h2>
</div>
 <div>

<p><a href="/fares-and-payments/fares2018/how-to-pay-and-where-to-buy-tickets-and-oyster/pay-as-you-go/touching-in-and-out">Touch your Oyster card in</a> at the start of your journey and <a href="/fares-and-payments/fares2018/how-to-pay-and-where-to-buy-tickets-and-oyster/pay-as-you-go/touching-in-and-out">touch out</a> at the end on yellow card readers to pay the right fare. Only touch in on buses and trams.</p>

<p>If you only have pay as you go credit on your Oyster card, you can lend it to someone else. Two people can't use the same contactless or Oyster card for a journey.</p>

<p>If you have a Travelcard, Bus &amp; Tram Pass or discount added to your Oyster card, you can't lend it to someone else.</p>

<h2>Where to buy</h2>

<p>Find out <a href="/fares-and-payments/fares2018/how-to-pay-and-where-to-buy-tickets-and-oyster/buying-tickets-and-oyster">where to buy an Oyster card</a>.</p>

<h2>Create an account</h2>

<p>Create a <a href="http://contactless.tfl.gov.uk/">contactless and Oyster account</a> and add your Oyster card, to:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Check your pay as you go credit and top up</li>
	<li>Check your payment and journey history</li>
	<li>Report your card if it's lost or stolen so no one else can use it</li>
	<li>Apply for refunds</li>
	<li>Pay unpaid fares</li>
</ul>

<h2>Download the app</h2>

<p>Our free <a href="/fares-and-payments/fares2018/how-to-pay-and-where-to-buy-tickets-and-oyster/tfl-oyster-and-contactless-app">TfL Oyster and contactless app</a> lets you manage your Oyster card on the go.</p>

<h2>Register your Oyster card</h2>

<p>If you don't register your card and you lose it, your pay as you go credit, Travelcard or Bus &amp; Tram Pass won't be refunded.</p>

<p>You need to register your Oyster card if you want to buy Travelcards and Bus &amp; Tram Passes for longer than a month.</p>

<p>Register your card now with a <a href="https://contactless.tfl.gov.uk/">contactless and Oyster account</a>.</p>

<p>Or, fill out a registration form at:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Your local <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/maps/oyster-ticket-stops">Oyster Ticket Stop</a></li>
	<li>Tube, London Overground, TfL Rail and some National Rail stations</li>
	<li><a href="/travel-information/visiting-london/getting-around-london/visitor-centres">Visitor Centres</a></li>
</ul>

<p><a href="/travel-information/visiting-london/visitor-oyster-card">Visitor Oyster cards</a> can't be registered.</p>

<h2>Pay as you go fares</h2>

<p>You can check your fare on our <a href="/fares-and-payments/fares2018/find-fares/tube-and-rail-fares/single-fare-finder">single fare finder</a>.</p>

<p>Travel as much as you like in one day and we'll <a href="/fares-and-payments/fares2018/find-fares/tube-and-rail-fares/pay-as-you-go-caps">cap your fare</a> so you don't pay more.</p>

